---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'contact@worldtvchannels.com';
---
<Base
  title="Terms of Use — World TV Channels"
  description="Terms of use for the World TV Channels website."
>
  <article class="container legal">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: 26 May 2026</p>

    <p>
      By using <strong>World TV Channels</strong> (the website, referred to here as
      “the service”) you agree to these terms. If you do not agree with any of
      them, please do not use the service.
    </p>

    <h2>1. The service is provided “as is”</h2>
    <p>
      The service is provided <strong>“as is”</strong>, without warranties of any
      kind, express or implied. We do not guarantee that:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>all TV channels will always be available;</li>
      <li>streaming quality will be uninterrupted;</li>
      <li>the service will work without errors on every device;</li>
      <li>the channel catalogue will remain unchanged.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. TV content</h2>
    <p>
      The service does not create, host or distribute TV content. It acts solely
      as an <strong>aggregator</strong> that plays publicly available third-party
      streams operated by the respective channels. Channel listings are sourced
      from the open
      <a href="https://github.com/iptv-org/iptv" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">iptv-org</a>
      project.
    </p>
    <p>
      All rights to the broadcast content (programmes, films, news, advertising
      and so on) belong to the <strong>respective channels</strong> and/or their
      licensors, not to us.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Responsibility for content</h2>
    <p>
      We are not responsible for the content broadcast by the channels accessible
      through the service — including its accuracy, legality, suitability or
      quality. Complaints or questions about specific content should be directed
      to the relevant channel.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Age requirement</h2>
    <p>
      The service is intended for <strong>users aged 13 and over</strong>. Adult
      (NSFW) channels are filtered out of the catalogue, but live TV content is
      not controlled by us, and some programming may contain language or themes
      unsuitable for younger viewers — parental discretion is advised.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Termination and changes</h2>
    <p>
      We reserve the right, at any time and without notice, to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>terminate access for a user who violates these terms;</li>
      <li>change the functionality or design of the service;</li>
      <li>discontinue the service entirely.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Advertising</h2>
    <p>
      The service is supported by advertising (Google AdSense is planned). By
      using the service you accept the display of such advertising. We do not
      control the content of the ads themselves. For details on data processing
      in advertising, see our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The name “World TV Channels”, the logo and the design of the site belong to
      the developers. Channel names and logos belong to their respective owners
      and are used only for identification. We do not redistribute the content
      broadcast by the channels — streams come directly from their own servers.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any indirect,
      incidental, consequential or special damages arising from the use of, or
      inability to use, the service — including but not limited to loss of data,
      interruption of service or lost profits.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Third-party links</h2>
    <p>
      The service includes links to and integrations with third parties — the
      iptv-org project, Google AdSense, and the channels whose streams it plays.
      We are not responsible for the content, policies or practices of these
      third parties.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms from time to time. Significant changes will be
      reflected by a new date at the top of this page.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For questions about these terms, please write to:
      <br />
      <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
